	Reentrant Monitor in Java (CTS Interview Question)
	-------------------------
	Java monitors are reentrant.
	The Java runtime system allows a thread to re-acquire a monitor that it already holds because Java monitors are reentrant. 
	It eliminate the possibility of a single thread deadlocking.
	
	Exa;
	
	class Reentrant {
		public synchronized void a() {
			b();
			System.out.println("here I am, in a()");
		}
		public synchronized void b() {
			System.out.println("here I am, in b()");
		}
	}
	Reentrant contains two synchronized methods: a and b. 
	The first synchronized method, a, calls the other synchronized method, b.

	
